column1: 4181343000,Esophageal cancer,"Overview: Esophageal cancer is most commonly of adenocarcinoma, but in the past it used to be squamous cell carcinoma. Presentation: progressive dysphagia and weight lossAssessment: endoscopy, radiology, histopathologyPlan: depends on the stage, especially if local, locally advanced, unresectable, inoperable etcPrognosis: depends on the stage","{
